AbleCredit Android SDK — Integration & API 
Documentation
Version: 1.0
Last Updated: November 2025
1. Overview
This document describes how to integrate the AbleCredit Android SDK 
(SdkManager) and details all publicly available SDK methods.
2. Gradle Plugins & Dependencies
Add these plugins at the top of your module-level Gradle file:
plugins {
    alias(libs.plugins.android.application)
    alias(libs.plugins.kotlin.android)
    id("org.jetbrains.kotlin.kapt")
    id("kotlin-parcelize")
}
Add the required dependencies:
// Core libraries
implementation("androidx.core:core-ktx:1.13.1")
implementation("androidx.appcompat:appcompat:1.7.0")
implementation("com.google.android.material:material:1.12.0")
// Room Database
implementation("androidx.room:room-runtime:2.6.1")
implementation("androidx.room:room-ktx:2.6.1")
kapt("androidx.room:room-compiler:2.6.1")
// Coroutines
implementation("org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-core:1.8.1")
implementation("org.jetbrains.kotlinx:kotlinx-coroutines-android:1.8.1")
// Networking
implementation("com.squareup.okhttp3:okhttp:4.12.0")
implementation("com.squareup.okhttp3:logging-interceptor:4.12.0")
implementation("com.squareup.retrofit2:retrofit:2.11.0")
implementation("com.squareup.retrofit2:converter-gson:2.11.0")
// Location
implementation("com.google.android.gms:play-services-location:21.3.0")
// SDK AAR
implementation(files("libs/app-release.aar"))
3. SDK Configuration
The SDK maintains configuration internally. You can read it using:
Key Value
Method SdkManager.getSdkConfig()
Returns SdkConfig(apiKey, tenantId, userId, 
baseUrl)
SdkConfig fields:
Key Value
apiKey String? — API key used for 
authentication
tenantId String? — Partner tenant identifier
userId String? — Logged-in user identifier
baseUrl String? — API base URL
4. initialize()
Purpose: Initializes the SDK with credentials and sets up repositories. Must 
be called before using any SDK method.
Key Value
Method SdkManager.initialize(context, apiKey, 
tenantId, userId, baseUrl, onResult)
Callback onResult(status: Int, message: String)
Behavior Initializes Retrofit client and repository;
validates input fields.
SdkManager.initialize(
    context = this,
    apiKey = "API_KEY",
    tenantId = "TENANT_ID",
    userId = "USER_ID",
    baseUrl = "https://api.yourdomain.com/"
) { status, message ->
    if (status == 1) {
        // success
    } else {
        // failure
    }
}
5. createNewLoanCase()
Purpose: Creates a new loan application using the backend API via 
LoanRepository.
Key Value
Method SdkManager.createNewLoanCase(cont
ext, payload: LoanRequest, onResult: 
(LoanResponse?) -> Unit)
On success Returns LoanResponse and displays 
Toast with Loan ID
On failure Shows Toast 'Failed to create loan' and 
returns null
SdkManager.createNewLoanCase(context = this, payload = loanRequest) 
{ response ->
    if (response != null) {
        // Loan created successfully
    } else {
        // Creation failed
    }
}
6. recordAudio()
Purpose: Launches RecorderActivity to record audio for a given loan 
application. Optionally accepts an UploadStatusListener to receive upload 
progress or completion events.
Key Value
Method SdkManager.recordAudio(context: 
Context, loanApplicationId: String?, 
listener: UploadStatusListener? = null)
Navigates to RecorderActivity (extras: 
APPLICATION_ID, TITLE)
Validation Shows Toast if loanApplicationId is null 
or blank
Listener If provided, receives onUploadStarted(),
onUploadProgress(), 
onUploadCompleted(), 
onUploadFailed()
// Example: Recording with listener
SdkManager.recordAudio(
    context = this,
    loanApplicationId = "APP-202511",
    listener = object : UploadStatusListener {
        override fun onUploadStarted(id: String) {
            Log.d("Upload", "Started for $id")
        }
        override fun onUploadProgress(id: String, progress: Int) {
            Log.d("Upload", "Progress $progress% for $id")
        }
        override fun onUploadCompleted(id: String) {
            Log.d("Upload", "Completed for $id")
        }
        override fun onUploadFailed(id: String, error: String?) {
            Log.e("Upload", "Failed for $id: $error")
        }
    }
)
7. Photo Capture Sections
These methods open TagActivity for specific sections and fetch tag lists from
the stored application JSON.
Key Value
captureFamilyPhotos()Launches TagActivity for 'lifestyle_tags'
(Family Photos)
captureBusinessPhotos()Launches TagActivity for 
'business_tags' (Business Photos)
captureCollateralPhotos()Launches TagActivity for 
'collateral_tags' (Collateral Photos)
SdkManager.captureFamilyPhotos(context = this, loanApplicationId = "APP-123")
SdkManager.captureBusinessPhotos(context = this, loanApplicationId = "APP-123")
SdkManager.captureCollateralPhotos(context = this, loanApplicationId = 
"APP-123")
8. clear()
Purpose: Resets SDK internal state, clearing credentials and configuration.
Key Value
Method SdkManager.clear(context: Context)
Effect Resets apiKey, tenantId, userId, 
baseUrl and initialized flag
Toast Displays 'SDK cleared successfully'
SdkManager.clear(context = this)
9. Internal Notes & Tips
• Always call initialize() before using SDK features.
• Ensure CAMERA, RECORD_AUDIO, and STORAGE permissions are 
granted.
• Each capture method internally validates initialization and loan ID.
• Keep the AAR file inside app/libs/ and update Gradle reference if renamed.
• Network requests are handled asynchronously using Retrofit + Coroutines.
• If UploadStatusListener is provided, RecorderActivity will relay live upload
status.